### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

common, core

### Description

When you are using a `@defer` block to lazy load an heavy component inside your HTML, but then use `viewChild(HeavyComponent)` to retrieve its reference, it will prevent the `@defer` block from creating a new lazy loadable chunk for that component (there is a [Medium article](https://medium.com/@schnabelelisa0/why-your-angular-defer-block-isnt-lazy-loading-4-common-pitfalls-ed50d4fb2578) about this issue).

```html
<!-- app.html -->
@defer {
  <app-child-component />
}
```
```ts
// app.ts
export class App {
  protected readonly childComponent = viewChild(ChildComponent);
  constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      console.log(this.childComponent());
    });
  }
}
```

Compiled output is:

```true
Initial chunk files | Names         |  Raw size | Estimated transfer size
main-FNSXWQNQ.js    | main          | 206.77 kB |                56.52 kB
styles-5INURTSO.css | styles        |   0 bytes |                 0 bytes

                    | Initial total | 206.77 kB |                56.52 kB
```

I know you can simply fix the issue by using a string reference instead of a component reference:

```html
<!-- app.html -->
@defer {
  <app-child-component #ref />
}
```
```ts
// app.ts
export class App {
  protected readonly childComponent = viewChild<ChildComponent>('ref');
  constructor() {
    effect(() => {
      console.log(this.childComponent());
    });
  }
}
```

Which correctly creates a lazy loadable chunk for the child component:

```true
Initial chunk files | Names           |  Raw size | Estimated transfer size
chunk-DYBHTAWP.js   | -               | 121.91 kB |                36.22 kB
main-O6YHMBR4.js    | main            |  85.91 kB |                21.83 kB
styles-5INURTSO.css | styles          |   0 bytes |                 0 bytes

                    | Initial total   | 207.82 kB |                58.05 kB

Lazy chunk files    | Names           |  Raw size | Estimated transfer size
chunk-7WWAQ7BK.js   | child-component | 326 bytes |               326 bytes
```


### Proposed solution

If it's possible, it would be nice to be able to directly use `viewChild(ChildComponent)` & `viewChildren(ChildComponent)` and not lose the optimization made by `@defer` blocks.

Angular could maybe internally use a "component identifier", like the class name, and transparently transform this to something like: `viewChild<ChildComponent>('_ChildComponent')` so that we don't have to manually add string reference, which would be convenient when we have a lot of viewChild/Children in our codebase

### Alternatives considered

If it's not easily feasible, people can still use the string reference to optimize their chunks.

